  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cool Schools Lebanon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lebanese schools&apos; capacity is overstretched, as they are providing education to both local population and refugees. Often in two shifts per day. Drop-out rates are at risk of rising, due to insufficient water and sanitation in the schools to provide a clean and safe environment for girls and boys. This project aim is to strengthen the community&#x2019;s resilience and prevent waterborne diseases.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lebanon - areas that host Syrian refugees.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Netherlands Red Cross and Lebanese Red Cross</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Lebanese schools that host both children of Syrian refugee population and host communities. The project supports the water and sanitation structures in the schools, as well as promotion of hygiene practices among the pupils. With the help of the WASH in Schools II project, the LRC WASH team can thus promote safer hygiene practices, which is especially important in light of the COVID-19 pandemic.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will enable and ensure healthy and dignified educational conditions for students in Lebanese public schools whether they are Syrian refugees or from vulnerable Lebanese families through strengthened hygienic behaviors, provision of safe water, improved sanitary conditions, and environmentally sustainable interventions. The Lebanese Red Cross provides &apos;hardware&apos; support: repairing water tanks, toilets, assessing privacy and safety levels. In addition, &apos;software&apos; activities: hygiene promotion and installation of sanitation committees composed of school children.</narrative>
  </description>
